cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SI

The paper deals with mutual information, which is a widely used concept in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper discusses the distribution of mutual information and its application to feature selection for classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with data sets and classification, which suggests the sub-categories cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as possible options.
